⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Etecoons & Dachora
node MET · MET · ⟦The Etecoons & Dachora:MET:f0f49d⟧

WHO   — The Etecoons & Dachora — the gentle creatures
WHAT  — The silent teachers of Super Metroid — the Etecoons who demonstrate the Wall Jump without a word, the Dachora who shows the Shinespark — and the doomed innocents Samus can choose to save in the final escape from Zebes.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because not everything on Zebes is a monster; because the planet's tutors ask nothing and teach freely; and because, in the last minutes before the world detonates, mercy is a choice — and they deserve to live.
HOW   — By instinct and gentleness — the Etecoons scaling a vertical shaft to show the climb, the Dachora charging into a glowing sprint — and by trusting the armored stranger enough to flee with her to the ship.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We ask nothing and teach everything — and if you remember us in the fire, we will live.

